label.value: Head and Neck Cancer TNM Finding v8

value.value: A finding about one or more characteristics of head and neck cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v8 classification system.

label.value: Head and Neck Cancer Clinical TNM Finding v8

value.value: A clinical finding about one or more characteristics of head and neck cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v8 classification system.

label.value: Head and Neck Cancer Clinical Regional Lymph Nodes TNM Finding v8

value.value: A clinical finding about one or more characteristics of head and neck cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v8 classification system as they pertain to staging of regional lymph nodes.

label.value: Head and Neck Cancer cN2 TNM Finding v8

value.value: Head and neck cancer with metastasis in a single ipsilateral lymph node larger than 3 cm but not larger than 6 cm in greatest dimension and ENE (extranodal extension)(-); or metastases in multiple ipsilateral lymph nodes, none larger than 6 cm in greatest dimension and ENE(-); or metastases in bilateral or contralateral lymph nodes, none larger than 6 cm in greatest dimension, ENE(-). (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Head and Neck Cancer cN2a TNM Finding v8

value.value: Head and neck cancer with metastasis in a single ipsilateral or contralateral lymph node larger than 3 cm but not larger than 6 cm in greatest dimension and ENE(-). (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Head and Neck Cancer cN2b TNM Finding v8

value.value: Head and neck cancer with metastasis in multiple ipsilateral lymph nodes, none larger than 6 cm in greatest dimension and ENE(-). (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Head and Neck Cancer cN2c TNM Finding v8

value.value: Head and neck cancer with metastasis in bilateral or contralateral lymph nodes, none larger than 6 cm in greatest dimension and ENE(-). (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Head and Neck Cancer cN3 TNM Finding v8

value.value: Head and neck cancer with metastasis in a lymph node larger than 6 cm in greatest dimension and ENE(-); or metastases in a single ipsilateral lymph node ENE(+); or metastases in multiple ipsilateral, contralateral, or bilateral lymph nodes, any with ENE(+). (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Nuclear Matrix

value.value: A network of fibrillar structures within cell nuclei that may play a role in chromatin organization and the localization of proteins within the nucleus.

label.value: Head and Neck Cancer cN3a TNM Finding v8

value.value: Head and neck cancer with metastasis in a lymph node larger than 6 cm in greatest dimension and ENE(-). (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Head and Neck Cancer cN3b TNM Finding v8

value.value: Head and neck cancer with metastasis in a single ipsilateral lymph node ENE(+); or metastases in multiple ipsilateral, contralateral, or bilateral lymph nodes, any with ENE(+). (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Head and Neck Cancer Pathologic TNM Finding v8

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of head and neck cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v8 classification system.

label.value: Head and Neck Cancer Pathologic Regional Lymph Nodes TNM Finding v8

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of head and neck cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v8 classification system as they pertain to staging of regional lymph nodes.

label.value: Head and Neck Cancer pNX TNM Finding v8

value.value: Head and neck cancer in which the regional lymph nodes cannot be assessed.  (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Head and Neck Cancer pN0 TNM Finding v8

value.value: Head and neck cancer in which no regional lymph node metastases are detected. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Head and Neck Cancer pN1 TNM Finding v8

value.value: Head and neck cancer with metastasis in a single ipsilateral lymph node, 3 cm or smaller in greatest dimension and ENE (extranodal extension)(-). (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Head and Neck Cancer pN2 TNM Finding v8

value.value: Head and neck cancer with metastasis in a single ipsilateral lymph node 3 cm or smaller in greatest dimension and ENE(+); or metastasis in a single ipsilateral lymph node larger than 3 cm but not larger than 6 cm in greatest dimension and ENE(-); or metastases in multiple ipsilateral lymph nodes, none larger than 6 cm in greatest dimension and ENE(-); or metastases in bilateral or contralateral lymph nodes, none larger than 6 cm in greatest dimension, ENE(-). (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Head and Neck Cancer pN2a TNM Finding v8

value.value: Head and neck cancer with metastasis in a single ipsilateral lymph node 3 cm or smaller in greatest dimension and ENE(+); or metastasis in a single ipsilateral lymph node larger than 3 cm but not larger than 6 cm in greatest dimension and ENE(-). (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Head and Neck Cancer pN2b TNM Finding v8

value.value: Head and neck cancer with metastases in multiple ipsilateral lymph nodes, none larger than 6 cm in greatest dimension and ENE(-); (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Nuclear Membrane

value.value: The double-layer membrane structure enclosing the nucleus in eukaryotic cells. It separates the DNA of the cell from the cytosol. For exchange of material, for example, proteins and mRNA, it is punctured with numerous nuclear pores.

label.value: Head and Neck Cancer pN2c TNM Finding v8

value.value: Head and neck cancer with metastases in bilateral or contralateral lymph nodes, none larger than 6 cm in greatest dimension and ENE(-). (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Head and Neck Cancer pN3 TNM Finding v8

value.value: Head and neck cancer with metastasis in a lymph node larger than 6 cm in greatest dimension and ENE(-); or metastases in a single ipsilateral lymph node larger than 3 cm and ENE(+); or metastases in multiple ipsilateral, contralateral, or bilateral lymph nodes, any with ENE(+). (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Head and Neck Cancer pN3a TNM Finding v8

value.value: Head and neck cancer with metastasis in a lymph node larger than 6 cm in greatest dimension and ENE(-). (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Head and Neck Cancer pN3b TNM Finding v8

value.value: Head and neck cancer with metastasis in a single ipsilateral lymph node larger than 3 cm in greatest dimension and ENE(+); or metastases in multiple ipsilateral, contralateral, or bilateral lymph nodes, any with ENE(+). (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Interleukin-3 Receptor Subunit Alpha Positive

value.value: Indicates that interleukin-3 receptor subunit alpha expression has been detected in a sample.

label.value: Cervical Lymph Nodes and Unknown Primary Tumors TNM Finding v8

value.value: A finding about one or more characteristics of cervical lymph nodes and unknown primary tumors, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v8 classification system. It applies to squamous cell carcinoma and salivary gland carcinoma of all head and neck sites except HPV-related oropharynx cancer, nasopharynx cancer, melanoma, thyroid carcinoma, and sarcoma. Staging of the patient who presents with an occult primary tumor and EBV-unrelated and HPV-unrelated metastatic cervical lymphadenopathy is also included. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Unknown Primary Tumor Clinical Cervical Lymph Nodes TNM Finding v8

value.value: A clinical finding about one or more characteristics of an unknown primary tumor, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v8 classification system as they pertain to staging of cervical lymph nodes. It applies to patients who are treated with primary nonsurgical treatment without a cervical lymph node dissection. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Unknown Primary Tumor cN2 TNM Finding v8

value.value: Unknown primary tumor with metastasis in a single ipsilateral cervical lymph node larger than 3 cm but not larger than 6 cm in greatest dimension and ENE (extranodal extension)(-); or metastases in multiple ipsilateral cervical lymph nodes, none larger than 6 cm in greatest dimension and ENE(-); or metastases in bilateral or contralateral cervical lymph nodes, none larger than 6 cm in greatest dimension, ENE(-). (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Unknown Primary Tumor cN2a TNM Finding v8

value.value: Unknown primary tumor with metastasis in a single ipsilateral cervical lymph node larger than 3 cm but not larger than 6 cm in greatest dimension and ENE(-). (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Nuclear Pore

value.value: An octagonal opening, about 70 nm across, where the inner and outer membranes of the nuclear envelope are continuous.

label.value: Unknown Primary Tumor cN2b TNM Finding v8

value.value: Unknown primary tumor with metastases in multiple ipsilateral cervical lymph nodes, none larger than 6 cm in greatest dimension and ENE(-). (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Unknown Primary Tumor cN2c TNM Finding v8

value.value: Unknown primary tumor with metastases in bilateral or contralateral cervical lymph nodes, none larger than 6 cm in greatest dimension, ENE(-). (from AJCC 8th Ed.)
